gary_County_Zala_(2010-).svg|k\u00f6z\u00e9pre|20px]] <br/>[[Zala County|Zala]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[File:Coa_Hungary_Town_Budapest_big.svg|k\u00f6z\u00e9pre|20px]] <br/>[[Budapest|Budapest]]\n! rowspan=\"1\" |[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_Hungary.svg|k\u00f6z\u00e9pre|20px]] <br/>[[Magyarorsz\u00e1g|all]]\n|-\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n== Government response ==\n\nOn 7 March, national ceremonies marking the anniversary of the [[Hungarian Revolution of 1848|Hungarian Revolution]] on 15 March were cancelled. Other cities and towns made similar decisions.<ref name=\"h0307\">{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/kozelet/cikk/2020/03/07/elo-a-koronavirussal-kapcsolatban-tajekoztat-az-operativ-torzs |title=Biztons\u00e1gi okokb\u00f3l lemondta a korm\u00e1ny a m\u00e1rcius 15-\u00e9re tervezett k\u00f6zponti \u00fcnneps\u00e9get |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=7 March 2020 |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/belpolitika/cikk/2020/03/07/a-fopolgarmester-is-lemondja-a-marcius-15-i-unnepseget |title=A f\u0151polg\u00e1rmester is lemondja a m\u00e1rcius 15-i \u00fcnneps\u00e9get |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=7 March 2020 |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/belpolitika/cikk/2020/03/07/szeged-es-szekesfehervar-is-lemondja-a-marcius-15-i-unnepseget |title=Szeged \u00e9s Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r is lemondja a m\u00e1rcius 15-i \u00fcnneps\u00e9get |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=7 March 2020 |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://kaposvarmost.hu/hirek/kaposvari-hirek/2020/03/09/elmaradnak-a-kaposvari-unnepi-megemlekezesek.html|title=Elmaradnak a kaposv\u00e1ri \u00fcnnepi megeml\u00e9kez\u00e9sek, a z\u00e1szl\u00f3felvon\u00e1st megtartj\u00e1k|date=9 March 2020|publisher=Kaposv\u00e1r Most|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/veres.pal.miskolc/photos/a.665842443842225/846765355749932/|title=Veres P\u00e1l polg\u00e1rmester nyilatkozata|date=2020-03-09|work=Facebook|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> A job fair planned to be held between 18 and 19 March at the [[Budapest University of Technology and Economics|University of Technology and Economics]] was also postponed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/kozelet/cikk/2020/03/07/elhalasztjak-a-muegyetemi-allasborzet-a-koronavirus-miatt/ |title=Elhalasztj\u00e1k a M\u0171egyetemi \u00c1ll\u00e1sb\u00f6rz\u00e9t a koronav\u00edrus miatt |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=7 March 2020 |accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe frequency of disinfection on Budapest public transport vehicles has increased, and the rule about using only the first door for boarding has been suspended, to decrease crowding.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/belpolitika/cikk/2020/03/11/jarvanyvedelmi-lepeseket-vezet-be-budapest |title=J\u00e1rv\u00e1nyv\u00e9delmi l\u00e9p\u00e9seket vezet be Budapest |work=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=2020-03-11 |access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> On 13 March, similar rules regarding getting on public transport were introduced in Miskolc as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mvkzrt.hu/aktualis/pentektol-felfuggeszti-az-mvk-zrt-az-elsoajtos-felszallast|title=P\u00e9ntekt\u0151l felf\u00fcggeszti az MVK Zrt. az els\u0151ajt\u00f3s felsz\u00e1ll\u00e1st|publisher=MVK Zrt.|date=2020-03-12|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nThe National Ambulance Service has provided more ambulances across the country to make easier the handling of increasing patients.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/cikk/2020/03/08/minden-megyeben-es-a-fovarosban-is-plusz-kocsikat-allitott-szolgalatba-az-omsz/ |title=Minden megy\u00e9ben \u00e9s a f\u0151v\u00e1rosban is plusz kocsikat \u00e1ll\u00edtott szolg\u00e1latba az OMSZ |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=8 March 2020 |access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref> 145 beds were freed for this cause in Saint Ladislaus Hospital, belonging to South Pest Central Hospital. Their capacity is now 81 rooms with 189 beds. If these fill up, other hospitals, capable of handling this type of situation, will also be used for quarantine locations elsewhere in the country.<ref name=\"h0307\"/> Since 8 March visiting someone in a hospital or in any social institution which provides long-term stay has been prohibited.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/kozelet/cikk/2020/03/08/orszagos-latogatasi-tilalom-lepett-ervenybe |title=Orsz\u00e1gos l\u00e1togat\u00e1si tilalom l\u00e9pett \u00e9rv\u00e9nybe |publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3 |date=2020-03-08 |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>. [[Budapest Zoo and Botanical Garden]] as well as every thermal baths will remain closed from 16 March. Starting with the same day, [[BuBi]] may be used for 100 HUF.<ref>{{Cite web |title=F\u0151v\u00e1ros: bez\u00e1rnak az \u00f3vod\u00e1k, b\u00f6lcs\u0151d\u00e9k, f\u00fcrd\u0151k \u00e9s az \u00c1llatkert |url=https://index.hu/belfold/2020/03/14/hetfotol_fokozatosan_bezarnak_a_fovarosi_ovodak/ |work=index.hu |date=2020-03-14 |accessdate=2020-03-14 |language=hu |author=Z\u00e1borszky Ede}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March the Surgeon General announced that the National Safety Laboratory of National Health Security Center had successfully isolated COVID-19 from a Hungarian patient's sample, which it could use for researching vaccines from a Hungarian patient's sample, to be used for the researches and production of new vaccine in Hungary.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://24.hu/tudomany/2020/03/17/koronavirus-izolalasa-magyarorszag/ |title=Magyarok izol\u00e1lt\u00e1k a koronav\u00edrust \u2013 mit jelent ez? |accessdate=2020-03-18 |date=2020-03-17 |work=24.hu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/orszagos-tisztifoorvos-sikeresen-izolaltak-az-nnk-laborjaban-koronavirust |title=Orsz\u00e1gos tisztif\u0151orvos: sikeresen izol\u00e1lt\u00e1k az NNK laborj\u00e1ban a koronav\u00edrust |work=Koronav\u00edrus.gov.hu |date=2020-03-17 |access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> A consortium founded by Immunology Department at Faculty of Sciences of [[E\u00f6tv\u00f6s Lor\u00e1nd University]], Biological Institute at Science Faculty of [[University of P\u00e9cs]], [[Gedeon Richter (company)|Richter Gedeon]] and ImmunoGenes is involved in international biotechnological developments.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nepszava.hu/3070707_koronavirus--magyar-gyogyszerfejlesztes-kezdodik |title=Koronav\u00edrus \u2013 Magyar gy\u00f3gyszerfejleszt\u00e9s kezd\u0151dik |accessdate=2020-03-18 |date=2020-03-14 |publisher=N\u00e9pszava}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.portfolio.hu/gazdasag/20200317/exkluziv-reszleteket-tudtunk-meg-a-koronavirus-elleni-magyarorszagi-gyogyszer-fejleszteserol-419859 |title=Exkluz\u00edv r\u00e9szleteket tudtunk meg a koronav\u00edrus elleni magyarorsz\u00e1gi gy\u00f3gyszer fejleszt\u00e9s\u00e9r\u0151l |accessdate=2020-03-18 |date=2020-03-17 |work=portfolio.hu}}</ref> Imre Kacskovics, leader of Immunology Department of ELTE said, product currently under preparation at the first phase it won't be a vaccine, it provides only passive [[immunology|immunity]], but it won't be able to prepare the body to fight against virus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://index.hu/techtud/2020/03/17/magyar_gyogyszert_fejlesztenek_a_koronavirus_ellen/ |title=Magyar gy\u00f3gyszert fejlesztenek a koronav\u00edrus ellen |accessdate=2020-03-18 |date=2020-03-17 |publisher=Index.hu}}</ref> Some days after the successful isolation Bioinformatic Research Team of Szent\u00e1gothay J\u00e1nos Research Center at University of P\u00e9cs and the virologist experts of the university found the [[genome]] of new [[SARS-CoV-2]] human coronavirus available in Hungary.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://index.hu/techtud/2020/03/21/koronavirus_magyar_genom_pecsi_tudomanyegyetem/ |title=Megvan az els\u0151 magyar koronav\u00edrus genom |accessdate=2020-03-21 |work=index.hu|date=21 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/virologiapecs/photos/a.106975587548686/129214918658086/?type=3&theater |title=Virol\u00f3gia P\u00e9cs |accessdate=2020-03-21 |work=facebook.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Coronavirus protection Budapest 2020-03-19 12-11-14.jpg|thumb|Closed area on a trolleybus in Budapest]]\nOn 19 March [[Andrea B\u00e1rtfai-Mager]] Minister without portfolio, responsible for National Wealth and the team led by her prepared and accepted recommendations which were the basis of economic decisions published next day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kormany.hu/hu/tarca-nelkuli-miniszter-3/hirek/elfogadta-a-kormany-a-gazdasag-ujrainditasaert-felelos-akciocsoport-egyes-javaslatait |title=Elfogadta a korm\u00e1ny a gazdas\u00e1g \u00fajraind\u00edt\u00e1s\u00e1\u00e9rt felel\u0151s akci\u00f3csoport egyes javaslatait |accessdate=2020-03-19 |date=2020-03-19 |work=kormany.hu |publisher=Magyar Korm\u00e1ny}}</ref>\n\n===State of emergency===\nOn 11 March, the Hungarian government declared a state of emergency. While these periods usually last for 15 days (after which the state of emergency must be renewed by Parliament), Minister of the Prime Minister's Office [[Gergely Guly\u00e1s]] stated the measures may be in force indefinitely,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nepszava.hu/3070239_gulyas-az-operativ-torzs-veszelyhelyzet-elrendeleset-javasolja-a-kormanynak|title=Guly\u00e1s: az operat\u00edv t\u00f6rzs vesz\u00e9lyhelyzet elrendel\u00e9s\u00e9t javasolja a korm\u00e1nynak|date=2020-03-11|publisher=N\u00e9pszava|accessdate=2020-03-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.origo.hu/itthon/percrolpercre/20200311-koronavirus-operativ-torzs-tajekoztato.html|title=Koronav\u00edrus: Kihirdette a korm\u00e1ny a vesz\u00e9lyhelyzetet|date=2020-03-11|work=origo.hu|accessdate=2020-03-11}}</ref> as \"there is a consensus that the length of this period may be not only weeks, but months.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://index.hu/kultur/2020/03/11/esemeny_elmarad_veszhelyzet_kinai_koronavirus_magyarorszagon/|title=Bez\u00e1rnak a mozik, a sz\u00ednh\u00e1zak, minden nagyobb esem\u00e9ny elmarad Magyarorsz\u00e1gon|date=2020-03-11|publisher=Index.hu}}</ref> Public gatherings in an enclosed space with more than 100 people were prohibited, sporting events that could attract more than 500 spectators must be held [[Behind closed doors (sport)|behind closed doors]], and [[Student exchange program|foreign exchange programs]] were suspended. Universities were ordered to suspend in-person classes and switch to online courses.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.origo.hu/itthon/percrolpercre/20200311-koronavirus-operativ-torzs-tajekoztato.html|title=Koronav\u00edrus: Kihirdette a korm\u00e1ny a vesz\u00e9lyhelyzetet|date=2020-03-11|publisher=Origo|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://index.hu/belfold/2020/03/11/koronavirus_veszhelyzet_iskola_ovoda_bezaras_szunet_rendezvenyek_otthoni_karanten_kormany_sportesemenyek/|title=Vesz\u00e9lyhelyzetet rendelt el a korm\u00e1ny|date=11 March 2020|publisher=Index.hu|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://hirado.hu/belfold/kozelet/cikk/2020/03/11/elo-sajtotajekoztatot-tart-az-operativ-torzs|title=Vesz\u00e9lyhelyzetet hirdetett a korm\u00e1ny az orsz\u00e1g eg\u00e9sz\u00e9re|date=2020-03-11|publisher=H\u00edrad\u00f3|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\n\nElementary and high schools were initially excluded from closure, due to an initial assessment that COVID-19 did not have as serious of an impact to children.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> The Ministry of Human Capacities recommended that schools suspend field trips, open-air classes, and exchange programs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/emmi-minden-iskolai-programot-unnepseget-mondjanak-le-az-intezmenyek|title=Emmi: minden iskolai programot, \u00fcnneps\u00e9get mondjanak le az int\u00e9zm\u00e9nyek!|date=2020-03-11|work=koronavirus.gov.hu|accessdate=2020-03-11}}</ref> On 13 March during a radio interview, [[Prime Minister of Hungary|Prime Minister]] [[Viktor Orb\u00e1n]] stated that kindergarten was also excluded since parents would have to guarantee children's supervision, and teachers would be required to take unpaid leave.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://444.hu/2020/03/13/orban-szerint-biztosan-lesznek-csoportos-megbetegedesek-es-valoszinuleg-halalos-aldozatok-is.|title=Orb\u00e1n szerint biztosan lesznek csoportos megbeteged\u00e9sek, \u00e9s val\u00f3sz\u00edn\u0171leg hal\u00e1los \u00e1ldozatok is|author=Andr\u00e1s Kir\u00e1ly|date=2020-03-13|work=Magyar Jeti Zrt|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> That evening, Orb\u00e1n announced that elementary and high schools would be closed to in-person classes effective 16 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/megkezdodik-jarvanyugyi-mobil-kontenerkorhaz-epitese-kiskunhalason|title=Megkezd\u0151dik a j\u00e1rv\u00e1ny\u00fcgyi mobil kont\u00e9nerk\u00f3rh\u00e1z \u00e9p\u00edt\u00e9se Kiskunhalason|date=2020-03-15|work=Koronav\u00edrus.gov.hu|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> \n\nOn 16 March, Prime Minister Orb\u00e1n announced further restrictions, including ordering the cancellation of all events, and banning restaurants and cafes from operating beyond 3 p.m. Only grocery stores and pharmacies would be allowed to remain open past this time. In addition, it was announced that the country would allow entry to Hungarian citizens only.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.origo.hu/itthon/percrolpercre/20200316-akoronavirushelyzetrol-szol-az-orszaggyules-is.html|title=Orb\u00e1n Viktor is felsz\u00f3lal ma az Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9sben - k\u00f6vesse a fejlem\u00e9nyeket tud\u00f3s\u00edt\u00e1sunkban|date=2020-03-16|work=Origo|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.origo.hu/itthon/percrolpercre/20200316-akoronavirushelyzetrol-szol-az-orszaggyules-is.html|title=Orb\u00e1n Viktor is felsz\u00f3lal ma az Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9sben - k\u00f6vesse a fejlem\u00e9nyeket tud\u00f3s\u00edt\u00e1sunkban|date=2020-03-16|work=Origo|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> In spite of the notices issued by operational staff about responsible behaviour and moderation, a 30-year-old security guard shared fake news on YouTube regarding the pandemic. He was the subject of police action.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://index.hu/belfold/2020/03/15/youtube-vloger_budapest_lezar_rendorseg/ |title=Elkapt\u00e1k a youtube-vloggert, aki elkezdte a pletyk\u00e1t Budapest lez\u00e1r\u00e1s\u00e1r\u00f3l|trans-title=Captured youtube vlogger who started rumoring about closing down Budapest |access-date=2020-03-15 |date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==== Rule by decree ====\nOn 30 March, the [[National Assembly (Hungary)|National Assembly]] passed an act 137\u201353 that made the state of emergency indefinite and allowed Prime Minister Orb\u00e1n to [[rule by decree]] during it.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Walker|first=Shaun|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/hungary-jail-for-coronavirus-misinformation-viktor-orban|title=Hungary passes law that will let Orb\u00e1n rule by decree|date=30 March 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=3 April 2020|url-status=live|last2=Rankin|first2=Jennifer}}</ref> During the state of emergency, by-elections and national and local referendums must be postponed until after the conclusion of the state of emergency, and deliberate bodies of a local governments and national minority self-governments cannot be dissolved.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://njt.hu/translated/doc/J2020T0012P_20200331_FIN.pdf|title=Act XII of 2020 on the containment of coronavirus|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=Ministry of Justice Hungary|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref> The act also makes the deliberate distribution of [[Fake news|misleading information]] that obstructs responses to the pandemic punishable by up to five years in prison, and breaking quarantine punishable by up to three.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n\nThe bill faced opposition for containing indefinite restrictions on these powers, as well as concerns over the possibility that the \"fake news\" prohibition in the bill could be abused for censorship of dissenting opinions towards the government's response.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/hungary-pm-orban-sweeping-powers-tackle-coronavirus-200330135806981.html|title=Hungary's PM Orban gets sweeping powers to tackle coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=Al Jazeera|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://hungarytoday.hu/coronavirus-hungary-special-powers-orban-govt-vote/|title=Coronavirus: Special Powers Granted to Gov\u2019t to Fight Pandemic|date=2020-03-30|website=Hungary Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news|last=Rankin|first=Jennifer|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/31/hungary-emergency-law-incompatible-with-being-in-eu-say-meps-group-viktor-orban|title=Hungary's emergency law 'incompatible with being in EU', say MEPs group|date=2020-03-31|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 31 March, liberal [[Member of the European Parliament|members of European parliament]] voiced concerns that the bill was incompatible with belonging to the European Union. Without mentioning Hungary, [[European Commission]] [[President of the European Commission|president]] [[Ursula von der Leyen]] advised that measures for controlling the pandemic should be \"limited to what is necessary and strictly proportionate\", and \"not at the expense of our fundamental principles and values as set out in the treaties\".<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nOn 1 April, a joint statement was issued by 13 EU member states, stating that they were \"deeply concerned\" about emergency initiatives violating democracy, fundamental rights, and the rule of law. The statement did not explicitly refer to Hungary;<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bayer|first=Lili|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/viktor-orban-hungary-13-countries-deeply-concerned-over-rule-of-law/|title=13 countries \u2018deeply concerned\u2019 over rule of law|date=1 April 2020|work=Politico|access-date=3 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.government.nl/documents/diplomatic-statements/2020/04/01/statement-by-belgium-denmark-finland-france-germany-greece-ireland-italy-luxembourg-the-netherlands-portugal-spain-sweden|title=Statement by Belgium, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Portugal, Spain, Sweden|last=|first=|date=1 April 2020|website=Government of the Netherlands|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref> the country joined the statement the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kormany.hu/en/ministry-of-justice/news/statement-of-hungary-02042020|title=Statement by Hungary|last=|first=|date=2 April 2020|website=Website of the Hungarian government|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Travel and entry restrictions ===\nEntry restrictions were initially targeted towards countries with large numbers of cases; the country initially began to suspend admission of migrants from its transit zones on the Serbian border, citing the outbreak in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|Iran]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mandiner.hu/cikk/20200301_bakondi_magyarorszag_hatarozatlan_idore_felfuggeszti_az_illegalis_migransok_beengedeset_a_tranzitzonaba|title=Bakondi: Magyarorsz\u00e1g hat\u00e1rozatlan id\u0151re felf\u00fcggeszti az illeg\u00e1lis migr\u00e1nsok beenged\u00e9s\u00e9t a tranzitz\u00f3n\u00e1ba|date=1 March 2020|publisher=Mandiner|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> On 6 March, Hungary suspended the issuance of visas to Iranian citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portfolio.hu/gazdasag/20200306/uj-informaciok-jelentek-meg-a-magyarorszagi-koronavirus-helyzetrol-418413|title=\u00daj inform\u00e1ci\u00f3k jelentek meg a magyarorsz\u00e1gi koronav\u00edrus-helyzetr\u0151l|date=6 March 2020|publisher=Portfolio|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March, restrictions began to emerge on air traffic from Northern Italy due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|outbreak]] in the country.<ref name=\"h0307\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.origo.hu/itthon/20200308-a-budapesti-repter-hetfotol-milanobol-bergamobol-es-trevisobol-nem-fogad-jaratokat.html|title=H\u00e9tf\u0151t\u0151l Mil\u00e1n\u00f3b\u00f3l, Bergam\u00f3b\u00f3l \u00e9s Trevis\u00f3b\u00f3l nem fogad j\u00e1ratokat a budapesti rept\u00e9r|date=2020-03-08|publisher=Origo|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> On 11 March, pursuant to the state of emergency, Hungary barred entry into the country by foreign nationals via China, Iran, Italy and South Korea. Hungarian citizens would still be allowed to return, but would be required to undergo 14 days of self-isolation upon return. Border checks were also re-implemented at the Austrian and Slovenian borders, and the government suspended travel by its employees without prior approval.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" />  On 13 March, Israel was added after two Hungarian cases were tied to travel to the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/orban-viktor-2115-orakor-bejelentest-tesz-kovesse-eloben|title=Orb\u00e1n Viktor 21:15 \u00f3rakor bejelent\u00e9st tesz! K\u00f6vesse \u00e9l\u0151ben!|date=2020-03-13|work=Koronav\u00edrus.gov.hu|access-date=2020-03-13}}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, Hungary restricted entry into the country to citizens only.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hungarytoday.hu/coronavirus-orban-hungary-closes-borders/|title=Coronavirus \u2013 Orb\u00e1n: Hungary Closes Borders for All Passenger Transport, Gov\u2019t Bans All Events|date=2020-03-16|website=Hungary Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n=== Economic decisions for managing the emergency ===\n\n[[Mih\u00e1ly Varga]] Minister of Finance said the government had to react to the real needs of the economy, and they were still waiting for the feedback from the trade and industry chamber.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://infostart.hu/gazdasag/2020/03/10/varga-mihaly-a-jarvany-hatasainak-megfeleloen-fog-reagalni-a-kormany |title=Varga Mih\u00e1ly: a j\u00e1rv\u00e1ny hat\u00e1sainak megfelel\u0151en fog reag\u00e1lni a korm\u00e1ny |accessdate=2020-03-19 |date=2020-03-10 |work=infostart.hu}}</ref> On 18 March during the early afternooon hours Viktor Orb\u00e1n announced several upcoming decisions. Though he used his own Facebook page instead of the dedicated communication channels.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://muosz.hu/2020/03/18/a-muosz-a-kormanyzati-kommunikacio-sulyos-zavarairol/ | title=A M\u00daOSZ a korm\u00e1nyzati kommunik\u00e1ci\u00f3 s\u00falyos zavarair\u00f3l| date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\nThe decisions were as follow:\n\n* All due payments are suspended which are caused by loans to persons and companies. It is valid for capital and interest payment as well. This is in force up to the end of the year.\n*Short-term loans for companies are prolonged up to 30 June.\n*Loans delivered from 19 March may have a maximum 5% above the [[Hungarian National Bank]]\u2019s interest rate.\n*Government remits subsidiaries which should have to paid based on the number of employees on the fields of tourism, catering, leisure, sport, culture and personal taxi services. Employees working in these sectors do not have to pay a pension subsidiary and the fee for receiving the benefits of the health sector is the minimum fee declared in the act.\n*Taxi drivers subject to the Kata tax system are exempt from tax until 30 June.\n*Rental contracts which are in connection with the above listed sectors may not be abrogated, rental fees may not be increased.\n*Contribution to the development of tourism (a kind of tax) is suspended until 30 June.\n*Labour rules will be more flexible, to make agreements between employers and employees easier.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://magyarnemzet.hu/belfold/orban-viktor-az-embereket-es-vallalkozasokat-erinto-konnyiteseket-jelentett-be-7901309/ |title=Orb\u00e1n Viktor hitel-, ad\u00f3- \u00e9s j\u00e1rul\u00e9kfizet\u00e9si morat\u00f3riumot jelentett be |accessdate=2020-03-19 |date=2020-03-19 |publisher=Magyar Nemzet}}</ref>\n\nThe Order about these changes was published in the 18 March edition of [[Magyar K\u00f6zl\u00f6ny]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/megjelentek-kozlonyben-gazdasagi-intezkedesekrol-szolo-rendeletek |title=Megjelentek a k\u00f6zl\u00f6nyben a gazdas\u00e1gi int\u00e9zked\u00e9sekr\u0151l sz\u00f3l\u00f3 rendeletek |accessdate=2020-03-19 |date=2020-03-19 |work=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref> Mih\u00e1ly Varga Minister of Finance and representatives of Hungarian Banking Association had a meting regarding actions listed above.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://magyarnemzet.hu/gazdasag/folyamatos-lesz-az-egyeztetes-a-bankszovetseg-es-a-kormany-kozott-7905461/ |title=Folyamatos lesz az egyeztet\u00e9s a Banksz\u00f6vets\u00e9g \u00e9s a korm\u00e1ny k\u00f6z\u00f6tt |accessdate=2020-03-19 |date=2020-03-19 |publisher=Magyar Nemzet}}</ref>\n\n==Impact on sport==\nNearly all sport events were affected by the state of emergency introduced on 11 March. It banned all indoor events with at least 100 and every outdoor events with at least 500 participants. As a consequence the next 25th round of [[2019\u201320 Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I]] had to be made without spectators.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/mlsz-zart-kapusak-lesznek-a-magyarorszagi-merkozesek-hivatalos-2752435 |title=MLSZ: z\u00e1rt kapusak lesznek a magyarorsz\u00e1gi m\u00e9rk\u0151z\u00e9sek \u2013 hivatalos |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-11 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> Only 6 out of 55 member states of UEFA had open matches, which were free to visit.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/minden_mas_foci/koronavirus-europaban-mar-csak-ot-futballbajnoksag-megy-2752821 |title=Koronav\u00edrus: Eur\u00f3p\u00e1ban m\u00e1r csak hat futballbajnoks\u00e1g megy |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-14 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On 16 March there was a decision made about suspension of the championship, suspending all matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/mlsz-azonnali-hatallyal-felfuggesztettek-az-nb-i-es-meccseket-is-2753205 |title=MLSZ: azonnali hat\u00e1llyal felf\u00fcggesztett\u00e9k az NB I-es meccseket is |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March they ended Erste Liga 2019\u20132020 Hungarian ice hockey championship, which was at the semi-final stage,<ref>{{Cite web|title=A Fradi \u00e9s a Sportklub is bajnok az Erste Lig\u00e1ban|url=http://www.jegkorongblog.hu/2020/03/11/a-fradi-es-a-sportklub-is-bajnok-az-erste-ligaban/|date=2020-03-11|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> and the same decision was made about all other ice hockey championships in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|title=V\u00e9ge a szezonnak Magyarorsz\u00e1gon!|url=http://www.jegkorongblog.hu/2020/03/13/vege-a-szezonnak-magyarorszagon/|date=2020-03-13|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> All matches part of championships and cup series organised by the Hungarian Handball Association were suspended.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/kezilabda/kezilabda-az-mksz-felfuggesztette-a-magyar-bajnoksagokat-hivatalos-2752847 |title=K\u00e9zilabda: az MKSZ felf\u00fcggesztette a magyar bajnoks\u00e1gokat \u2013 hivatalos |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The same decision was made by the [[Hungarian Water Polo Federation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/vizilabda/vizilabda-az-ob-i-es-meccseket-es-a-korosztalyos-bajnokikat-is-halasztjak-2752863 |title=V\u00edzilabda: az ob I-es meccseket \u00e9s a koroszt\u00e1lyos bajnokikat is halasztj\u00e1k |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> Basketball and volleyball championships were also suspended.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/egyeb_csapat/roplabda-az-mrsz-aprilisig-felfuggesztette-a-magyar-bajnoksagot-2752817 |title=R\u00f6plabda: az MRSZ \u00e1prilisig felf\u00fcggesztette a magyar bajnoks\u00e1got |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/kosarlabda/koronavirus-szombattol-szunetel-a-kosarlabdaelet-magyarorszagon-2752805 |title=Koronav\u00edrus: szombatt\u00f3l sz\u00fcnetel a kos\u00e1rlabda\u00e9let Magyarorsz\u00e1gon |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The National Swimming Championship has also been prolonged.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/uszas/koronavirus-a-marcius-vegi-uszo-ob-t-is-elhalasztottak-2753167 |title=Koronav\u00edrus: a m\u00e1rcius v\u00e9gi \u00fasz\u00f3 ob-t is elhalasztott\u00e1k |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> The Hungarian Boxing Association announced the evacuation of participants from London, where qualification for the [[2020 Summer Olympics]] were ongoing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/okolvivas/okolvivas-evakualjak-sportoloinkat-londonbol-2753215 |title=\u00d6k\u00f6lv\u00edv\u00e1s: evaku\u00e1lj\u00e1k sportol\u00f3inkat Londonb\u00f3l|work=Nemzeti Sport Online |date=2020-03-16 |access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Hungarian Karate Federation announced that they temporally cancel [[karate]] contents part of the content calendar.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.karate.hu/Hirek/Ideiglenesen-elmaradnak-az-MKSZ-versenyei |title=Ideiglenesen elmaradnak az MKSZ versenyei! |access-date=2020-03-21 |date=March 2020  |publisher=Magyar Karate Szaksz\u00f6vets\u00e9g |work=karate.hu |language=Hungarian }}</ref> On 13 March they three \u00e9taps of [[2020 Giro d'Italia|Giro d\u2019Italia]] in the country have been cancelled,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Giro d'Italia: lemondt\u00e1k a magyarorsz\u00e1gi szakaszokat|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/kerekpar/giro-ditalia-lemondtak-a-magyarorszagi-szakaszokat-2752761|date=2020-03-13|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> On 17 March the most well-known Hungarian bicycle tour, [[2020 Tour de Hongrie|Tour de Hongrie]] has been moved from May to October.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Koronav\u00edrus: a Tour de Hongrie-t is elhalasztott\u00e1k|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/kerekpar/koronavirus-a-tour-de-hongrie-t-is-elhalasztottak-2753431|date=2020-03-17|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\nDue to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bulgaria|state of emergency]] in [[Bulgaria]], they banned all sport events in the country up to 29 March. As a result, the qualifying match between [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] and [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] has been postponed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/magyar_valogatott/koronavirus-elhalasztjak-a-bolgar-magyart-hivatalos-2752831 |title=Koronav\u00edrus: elhalasztj\u00e1k a bolg\u00e1r\u2013magyart \u2013 hivatalos! |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On 17 March, UEFA postponed the whole championship a year to 2021, which is scheduled to be held among other countries apart from Hungary.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/foci-eb-2020/uefa-megszuletett-a-dontes-elhalasztjak-az-eb-t-2753373 |title=UEFA: megsz\u00fcletett a d\u00f6nt\u00e9s, elhalasztj\u00e1k az Eb-t |work=Nemzeti Sport |date=2020-03-17 |access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n[[European Karate Federation]] informed Hungarian Karate Federation about the cancelling European Championship that year, planned to take place in [[Baku]] from 25 to 29 March. This championship is part of the qualification events to the Olympics.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.napi.hu/magyar_gazdasag/koronavirus-magyarorszag-lezaras-sport-program-halasztas.702130.html |title=Sorra halasztj\u00e1k el a j\u00e1rv\u00e1ny miatt a magyarorsz\u00e1gi rendezv\u00e9nyeket is |access-date=2020-03-21 |last=Szab\u00f3 | first = D\u00e1niel |date=2020-03-14 |publisher=www.napi.hu Online Kft. |work=[[Napi.hu]] |language=Hungarian }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.origo.hu/sport/egyeni/20200314-karate-elmarad-a-marcius-vegi-bakui-europa-bajnoksag.html?utm_source=hirkereso |title=Elmarad a m\u00e1rcius v\u00e9gi olimpiai kvalifik\u00e1ci\u00f3s karate Eur\u00f3pa-bajnoks\u00e1g |access-date=2020-03-21 |date=2020-03-14 |publisher=[[New Wave Media Group Kft.]] |work=[[Origo.hu]] |language=Hungarian }}</ref><!--\n\n== Cases ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders collapsed\" style=\"width: 100%;\"\n\n! scope=\"col\" | Case no.\n! scope=\"col\" | Cluster\n! scope=\"col\" | Date announced\n! scope=\"col\" | Status\n! scope=\"col\" | Source of infection\n! scope=\"col\" | Origin of infection\n! scope=\"col\" | Nationality\n! scope=\"col\" | Detection location\n! scope=\"col\" | Treatment facility\n! scope=\"col\" | Sex\n! scope=\"col\" | Age\n! scope=\"col\" | Source\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n| 4 March 2020\n| {{Failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{unofficial|Imported case}}\n| {{flag|Iran}}\n| {{flag|Iran}}\n| {{flag|Budapest}}\n| {{Success|[[Healthcare in Hungary|Saint Ladislaus Hospital]]}}\n| Male\n| 36 years\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite news |last1=Heinrich |first1=Mark |last2=Dunai |first2=Marton |last3=Lawrence |first3=Janet |title=Hungary confirms first two coronavirus cases |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-hungary/hungary-confirms-first-two-coronavirus-cases-idUSKBN20R2RA |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Reuters |agency=Reuters |issue=Mar2020 |publisher=Reuters |date=4 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"9\" | One of two Iranian students who had travelled [[Iran|home]] for the Iranian new y