ntcover&pg=GBS.PP3|title=Veer Raghoji Bhangre / Nachiket Prakashan: \u0935\u0940\u0930 \u0930\u093e\u0918\u094b\u091c\u0940 \u092d\u093e\u0902\u0917\u0930\u0947|last=\u0922\u094b\u092e\u0923\u0947|first=\u0938\u094c \u0936\u093f\u0932\u094d\u092a\u093e|date=21 April 2016|publisher=Nachiket Prakashan|language=mr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=GSa5blriOYcC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=raghoji+bhangre#v=onepage&q=raghoji%20bhangre&f=false|title=Environment and Ethnicity in India, 1200-1991|last=Guha|first=Sumit|date=2 November 2006|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521028707|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Ambigara Chowdaiya]], saint, poet and  social critic in the 12th century in the India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ambigaradevelopment.karnataka.gov.in/info-1/About+Us/en|title=About Us - Nijasharana Ambigara Choudaiya Development Corporation|website=ambigaradevelopment.karnataka.gov.in|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Reporter|first=Staff|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/cm-led-delegation-to-seek-inclusion-of-kolikabbaligas-into-sts-list/article30895798.ece|title=CM-led delegation to seek inclusion of Koli/Kabbaligas into STs list|date=2020-02-23|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-03-25|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n*[[Ramesh Patil]], former member of [[Maharashtra Legislative Council]] and president of [[Koli Mahasangh]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/mumbai/mumbai-bjp-rallies-fishermen-opposing-coastal-road-project-5538710/|title=Mumbai: BJP rallies around fishermen opposing coastal road project|date=15 January 2019|website=The Indian Express|access-date=28 April 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Govindas Ramdas]], Indian revolutionary<ref name=\":16\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SM9jDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT127|title=Political Mobilization and Identity in Western India, 1934-47|last=Krishan|first=Shri|date=7 April 2005|publisher=SAGE Publishing India|isbn=9789352803071}}</ref>\n*[[Parshottambhai Solanki]], former minister of Fishery in the Government of Gujarat<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ahmedabad/solanki-skips-cabinet-meeting-ups-ante/articleshow/62357681.cms|title=Koli leader Parshottam Solanki skips cabinet meeting, ups ante - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mahendra Munjapara]], [[Member of parliament]] from [[Surendranagar (Lok Sabha constituency)]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/bjp-goes-safe-retains-14-mps-but-drops-mp-devji-fatehpara-2012103|title=Surendranagar MP Devji Fatehpara Dropped From BJP List, Hits Out At Party|website=NDTV.com|access-date=15 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/ahmedabad/report-gujarat-14-sitting-mps-in-bjp-s-first-list-of-15-2733158|title=Gujarat: 14 sitting MPs in BJP's first list of 15|date=25 March 2019|website=DNA India|access-date=15 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/bjp-announces-15-lok-sabha-candidates-in-gujarat-drops-surendranagar-mp/articleshow/68541330.cms|title=BJP announces 15 Lok Sabha candidates in Gujarat, drops Surendranagar MP {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=23 Mar|first=PTI {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|access-date=15 June 2019|last3=Ist|first3=22:59}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://deshgujarat.com/2019/03/23/who-is-dr-mahendra-munjapara-a-surprise-name-in-bjp-ls-candidate-list-for-gujarat/|title=Who is Dr. Mahendra Munjapara, a surprise name in BJP LS candidate list for Gujarat|date=23 March 2019|website=DeshGujarat|access-date=15 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/elections/lok-sabha-elections-bjp-announces-15-candidates-in-gujarat-drops-surendranagar-mp/1525141/|title=Lok Sabha elections: BJP announces 15 candidates in Gujarat, drops Surendranagar MP|date=23 March 2019|website=The Financial Express|access-date=15 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|